  "market_context": "Intraday session on 26/10/2023: Asia range formed accumulation, London swept Asia high (manipulation), then price retested the New Day Opening Gap (NDOG) at NY open before initiating a bearish distribution leg.",
  "key_observation": "Price consolidated near the NDOG before a down-close candle triggered aggressive displacement lower; the manipulation leg (low-to-high sweep) was used to project standard deviation targets aligning with equal lows and London low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified the daily AMD structure—Asia accumulation, London manipulation (sweep of Asia high), and NY distribution phase reaching into the NDOG.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to 1-minute chart to locate the NDOG zone (14420–14460) and observed consolidation prior to NY open, followed by an aggressive down-close candle breaking the range.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed further displacement downward with a large black candle at 09:38, signaling valid bearish distribution initiation.",
    "Step 4: Anchored standard deviation projection from the manipulation low (14220–14240 area) to the manipulation high (NDOG top ~14460) to generate targets at -2.5σ (~14240–14260) and -4.5σ (~14220–14240).",
    "Step 5: Verified confluence: -2.5σ target aligned with equal lows; -4.5σ target aligned with the London session low, both marked as PD arrays."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price hit the -1σ target, retraced into an up-close candle, then continued lower to sweep the -2.5σ zone (equal lows) and approached the -4.5σ (London low) target.",
  "lessons": "When price retests the NDOG within a daily AMD structure, the manipulation leg defines precise distribution targets via standard deviation; confluence with existing PD arrays (equal lows, London low) increases validity and provides high-probability exit zones.",
